      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Globo Cabo , a unit of Brazil's largest media group, Organizacoes Globo, acquired control of the cable television operator Net Sul for about $900 million in stock and debt. The deal gives Globo Cabo greater access to 27 cities in south Brazil and increases its subscribers in Brazil by a third, to almost 1.4 million, making it Latin America's largest cable television provider. Recently, Globo Cabo has been taking on investors to pay down debt and expand into telecommunications and the Internet.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
